- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributional semantics and entailment, which are both topics within natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a vector-space model and uses a mean-field approximation for inference, which are both techniques commonly used in machine learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with modeling semantic similarity and entailment, which are both important topics in AI.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with word distributions in contexts, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks such as document classification and clustering.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but it may be relevant to the approximation procedures used in the model.
